### Question 3

**Configure Squid as a proxy server to enable internet access for your IP subnet. Implement rules to block all web access during 9:00 AM to 6:00 PM and allow access to cdac.in at all times.**

### Commands

Install Squid:

```bash
sudo dnf install squid -y
```

or

```bash
sudo apt install squid -y
```

Edit configuration:

```bash
sudo vi /etc/squid/squid.conf
```

Add the following lines:

```ini
acl mynetwork src 192.168.74.0/24
acl cdac dstdomain .cdac.in
acl officehours time 09:00-18:00

http_access allow mynetwork cdac
http_access deny mynetwork officehours
http_access allow mynetwork

http_port 3128
```

Validate configuration:

```bash
sudo squid -k parse
```

Start and enable Squid:

```bash
sudo systemctl enable squid
sudo systemctl restart squid
sudo systemctl status squid
```

Open firewall port:

```bash
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=3128/tcp
sudo firewall-cmd --reload
```

Configure client browser proxy:

```text
Proxy IP: <Squid_Server_IP>
Port: 3128
```

Test:

```bash
curl -x http://<Squid_Server_IP>:3128 http://cdac.in
```
